1
00:00:05,200 --> 00:00:15,000
Doctor Who (1963) 04x09  The Evil of the Daleks (Episode 3)
《神秘博士》老版第四季第九集 《Daleks 的邪恶》 (第三部分)

2
00:00:18,200 --> 00:00:21,000
【翻译】巴蛮子sz

3
00:00:21,200 --> 00:00:24,000
【时间轴】巴蛮子sz

4
00:00:24,200 --> 00:00:27,000
【校对】巴蛮子sz

5
00:00:27,200 --> 00:00:30,000
<i>基于 opentitles.org 英文字幕翻译</i>

6
00:00:30,200 --> 00:00:33,006
Sincro: wyxchari

7
00:00:33,084 --> 00:00:37,005
DALEK 1: The humans have been told to begin the test.
已经通知人类开始实验

8
00:00:37,297 --> 00:00:40,521
DALKE 2: Any delay will result in death.
任何人拖延都将处死

9
00:00:40,795 --> 00:00:42,926
DALEK 2: There will be no delay!
不允许有拖延!

10
00:00:43,942 --> 00:00:47,451
MAXTIBLE: Mollie, Mollie. Mr. McCrimmon has been kidnapped!
Mollie, Mollie. McCrimmon先生被绑架了！

11
00:00:47,942 --> 00:00:51,451
MAXTIBLE: It means the end of us unless we can find him quickly.
这意味着我们都将完蛋了, 除非赶紧找到他

12
00:00:50,805 --> 00:00:56,899
<i>(The Doctor shows them some straw he has found, then walks off.)</i>
<i>(博士把他发现的一些稻草拿给他们看, 然后走开了)</i>

13
00:00:51,805 --> 00:00:52,899
DOCTOR: Straw.
稻草

14
00:00:53,243 --> 00:00:54,408
WATERFIELD: I beg your pardon?
你说什么？

15
00:00:54,694 --> 00:00:55,656
DOCTOR: A piece of straw.
一小截稻草

16
00:01:02,478 --> 00:01:04,549
TOBY: Had a cosy little sleep, young swell?
小觉睡的还舒服吧, 年轻人？

17
00:01:06,713 --> 00:01:11,301
TOBY: Lively, is it? Maybe you'd like to sleep again? 
醒了吧, 对不？是不是还想睡一觉？

18
00:01:11,428 --> 00:01:14,139
TOBY: I've got Mr. Nod here. He'll have you snorin' as good as ever.
我这里有位“点头”先生, 他会让你的呼噜震天响的

19
00:01:14,355 --> 00:01:15,551
JAMIE: What do you want?
你想要怎么样？

20
00:01:15,884 --> 00:01:18,250
TOBY: I'm to be well paid. Have no fear of that.
我会得到很好的报酬, 我不怕那个。

21
00:01:18,500 --> 00:01:20,591
JAMIE: Oh, and for what? I don't know you.
哦, 得到什么报酬？ 我不认识你

22
00:01:23,839 --> 00:01:24,998
TOBY: This your man, sir?
这是你要的人吧, 先生？

23
00:01:25,356 --> 00:01:27,446
TERRALL: Toby! What in Hades have you done?
Toby! 你到底干了什么？

24
00:01:28,432 --> 00:01:31,049
TOBY: Why, I, uh... brought 'im from the house, like you said.
为什么。。。我把他从房子里带过来了啊, 你这么说的

25
00:01:31,254 --> 00:01:32,519
TERRALL: I said nothing of the kind.
我可没说这样的话

26
00:01:32,930 --> 00:01:37,590
TOBY: Well ya did, sir! Honest ya did.
A guinea ya promised me.
你说过, 先生！你真的说过。许诺给我一基尼呢

27
00:01:37,930 --> 00:01:41,590
TOBY: I... I done what ya said. You don't get outta payin'.
我。。我已经做了你要求的, 你别想不给钱

28
00:01:41,814 --> 00:01:43,388
TERRALL: Be careful how you speak to me, Toby!
注意你跟我说话的方式, Toby!

29
00:01:45,815 --> 00:01:48,077
TERRALL: There's your money. Get out!
这是给你的钱, 出去！

30
00:01:49,805 --> 00:01:54,899
<i>(Toby picks up the coin Terrall threw, then leaves.)</i>
<i>(Toby 捡起 Terrall 扔下的硬币, 离开了)</i>

31
00:02:07,534 --> 00:02:08,873
TERRALL: Where's Toby?
Toby 哪儿去了？

32
00:02:09,014 --> 00:02:12,489
JAMIE: You just sent him about his business.
Look, what's the matter? Are you all right?
你刚把他打发走了啊。这到底怎么回事？你还好吗？

33
00:02:13,430 --> 00:02:14,984
TERRALL: Where's Victoria Waterfield?
Victoria Waterfield 在哪儿？

34
00:02:15,212 --> 00:02:15,805
JAMIE: I don't know.
我不知道

35
00:02:16,255 --> 00:02:17,243
TERRALL: Yes, you do.
知道

36
00:02:17,481 --> 00:02:18,765
JAMIE: I tell you, I don't even know her!
我告诉你, 我都不认识她

37
00:02:19,828 --> 00:02:22,876
TERRALL: You're in the house, a friend of Maxtible's. You must know!
你在这个房子里, 你是 Maxtible 的朋友, 你肯定知道！

38
00:02:23,058 --> 00:02:25,005
JAMIE: No, listen, I'm te...
不, 听我说, 我说的是。。。

39
00:02:25,058 --> 00:02:30,005
<i>(A metal attachment can be see on Terrall's neck.)</i>
<i>(Terrall 的脖子上可以见到金属物件在反光)</i>

40
00:02:32,275 --> 00:02:34,249
TERRALL: Ha, I must apologize for that villain Toby.
哈, 我必须为那个恶棍 Toby 的事向你道歉。

41
00:02:34,475 --> 00:02:37,749
TERRALL: He was telling lies, of course. I shall escort you to the house.
当然, 他说的都是谎言。我护送你回房子里去

42
00:02:37,925 --> 00:02:40,007
JAMIE: Uh, You... you... you just asked me about Victoria Waterfield.
哦, 你。。。你。。你刚才还在问我 Victoria Waterfield 的事情

43
00:02:40,272 --> 00:02:44,929
TERRALL: Now, she's in Paris. I'm afraid I haven't introduced myself - Arthur Terrall.
现在, 她还在巴黎呢。恐怕我还没有介绍我自己 - Arthur Terrall

44
00:02:45,107 --> 00:02:49,601
JAMIE: Well, never mind about that. Did you or did you not
ask that man to knock me on the head and bring me in here?
哦, 先别管那个了。你有还是没有, 叫那个人把我打晕再把我带过来？

45
00:02:49,765 --> 00:02:52,072
TERRALL: I, oh...certainly not!
我, 噢。。。当然没有

46
00:02:52,743 --> 00:02:53,386
JAMIE: Doctor
博士

47
00:02:53,486 --> 00:02:58,486
TERRALL: Oh. I see you're in good hands now.
I won't detain you any further. 
哦, 我看你现在碰到朋友了。我就不再耽误你了。

48
00:02:58,586 --> 00:02:59,586
TERRALL: Good day, Doctor.
日安, 博士

49
00:02:59,706 --> 00:03:00,749
DOCTOR: Oh, good day to you.
哦, 你也日安

50
00:03:01,025 --> 00:03:03,671
JAMIE: He's mad. Stark, staring mad!
他疯了, 他完全疯了

51
00:03:03,935 --> 00:03:06,549
TERRALL: Yes, I know. I was listening. Let's have a look at
that head of yours. Come along.
是的, 我知道, 刚才我听到了。我们来看看你的头吧, 过来

52
00:03:07,249 --> 00:03:12,149
JAMIE: Look, it's all right, Doctor. One minute he says this,
the next minute he says that. Can you make it out, Doctor?
哦, 问题不大, 博士。前一分钟他在说这个, 后一分钟他又说那个。你搞明白了吗？ 

53
00:03:12,349 --> 00:03:17,149
JAMIE: I'm knocked on the head and I'm brought in here.
Then that man Terrall enters and denies having ordered the other man to do it.
我被人敲晕了脑袋, 带到了这里。那个Terrall 进来之后否认是他让那个人干的。

54
00:03:17,349 --> 00:03:23,149
JAMIE: Well, then he changes, and starts asking about Victoria Waterfield
and in the next breath, he tells me she's in Paris!
然后, 他又变了, 开始问 Victoria Waterfield 的事情, 下一秒钟他又告诉我她在巴黎！

55
00:03:23,349 --> 00:03:25,230
DOCTOR: I know what's happened to Victoria.
我知道 Victoria 发生了什么事

56
00:03:25,395 --> 00:03:26,191
JAMIE: What has?
什么事？

57
00:03:26,465 --> 00:03:28,281
DOCTOR: She's a prisoner of the Daleks.
她成了 Daleks 的囚徒

58
00:03:31,247 --> 00:03:32,489
DALEK: Hurry!
快点！

59
00:03:34,487 --> 00:03:44,412
VICTORIA: Why am I being moved?
Are you taking me back to my father?
为什么要转移我？你们要带我回到我父亲那里吗？

60
00:03:44,996 --> 00:04:01,256
DALEK: No, you are being moved. Pick up your cover. Follow.
不, 只是给你换个地方。带上你的外套。跟上。

61
00:03:50,058 --> 00:03:55,005
<i>(She picks up a bundle of clothes from the bed and stands up.)</i>
<i>(她从床上拿起一叠衣服, 站了起来)</i>

62
00:04:01,334 --> 00:04:07,625
DALEK: Do not be afraid. You are not to be exterminated.
不用害怕, 你不会被终结掉

63
00:04:09,058 --> 00:04:14,005
<i>(She follows the Dalek down the corridor.)</i>
<i>(她跟在 Dalek 后面沿着走廊前行)</i>

64
00:04:14,058 --> 00:04:18,005
<i>(A second Dalek arrives.)</i>
<i>(有一个 Dalek 过来了)</i>

65
00:04:18,273 --> 00:04:20,125
DALEK: Do not delay.
不要磨蹭

66
00:04:22,058 --> 00:04:27,005
<i>(She walks down the corridor between the Daleks.)</i>
<i>(她从两个 Dalek 之间走过, 沿着走廊往前走)</i>

67
00:04:35,058 --> 00:04:39,005
<i>(Victoria stops to look out of a window.)</i>
<i>(Victoria 停下来, 往窗外望去)</i>

68
00:04:40,766 --> 00:04:42,088
DALEK: Move.
走

69
00:04:50,437 --> 00:04:56,201
<i>(Jamie enters the room unobserved and listens from behind a screen.)</i>
<i>(Jamie 前无声息地进了房间, 在一个屏风后面躲着)</i>

70
00:04:51,437 --> 00:04:53,201
WATERFIELD: You've warned him - told him about the Daleks?
你警告他了, 把 Daleks 的事情告诉他了？

71
00:04:53,383 --> 00:04:54,028
DOCTOR: Yes, of course I did!
是的, 我当然会这样

72
00:04:54,262 --> 00:04:55,332
WATERFIELD: But you were expressly told...
但你被命令禁止。。。

73
00:04:55,571 --> 00:04:56,415
DOCTOR: Oh, fiddlesticks!
哦, 别胡说！

74
00:04:56,778 --> 00:05:00,504
DOCTOR: Bosh! Jamie will cooperate. You may be certain of that.
胡说！ Jamie 会合作的。这个事情你可以放心

75
00:05:00,676 --> 00:05:01,806
WATERFIELD: Are you sure?
你确定吗？

76
00:05:01,974 --> 00:05:08,817
DOCTOR: Yes, perfectly sure. Jamie will do everything he is asked to do.
Now come along, we must go and find Maxtible.
是的, 完全确定。你让 Jamie 做任何事情, 他都会去做。来吧, 我们去找 Maxtible

77
00:05:31,778 --> 00:05:36,156
DALEK: The female human being has been moved.
那个人类女性已经被转移

78
00:05:36,414 --> 00:05:38,480
MAXTIBLE: Everything is prepared.
一切已经准备就绪

79
00:05:38,698 --> 00:05:41,710
DALEK: The testing equipment is ready?
实验设备准备好了吗？

80
00:05:41,952 --> 00:05:47,887
MAXTIBLE: I think you will be pleased with the man,
I've had specially brought from London. Ah, he works in my house.
我像你会对这个人满意的, 我特意把他从伦敦带过来, 他在那边一直帮我做事

81
00:05:48,163 --> 00:05:49,152
DALEK: Show me!
带来见我

82
00:05:53,375 --> 00:05:57,503
MAXTIBLE: You will understand that he is rather simple.
你要明白他是一个相当简单的人

83
00:05:53,375 --> 00:06:03,603
MAXTIBLE: He's quite dumb, but, uh... that has its advantages for us.
他很笨, 不过。。。对我们而言这是个优势

84
00:06:03,875 --> 00:06:05,603
MAXTIBLE: His mind is, how shall I say, undeveloped.
他的大脑, 怎么说呢, 不太发达

85
00:06:05,875 --> 00:06:10,603
MAXTIBLE: He will not understand you, the Daleks.
Uh, I mean he will be terrified of you.
他搞不懂你们 Daleks。我是说, 他会害怕你们

86
00:06:10,839 --> 00:06:11,195
DALEK: Show me.
带来见我

87
00:06:11,898 --> 00:06:12,889
MAXTIBLE: Ohh, I beg your pardon, uh...
哦, 我很抱歉

88
00:06:13,039 --> 00:06:17,195
<i>(The Dalek enters the cabinet and closes the door.)</i>
<i>(Dalek 进了柜子, 关上了门)</i>

89
00:06:20,413 --> 00:06:21,320
MAXTIBLE: Kemel!

90
00:06:29,912 --> 00:06:34,827
MAXTIBLE: Will you come with me?
你跟我来

91
00:06:34,912 --> 00:06:44,827
MAXTIBLE: I want you to stand here.
No, no, no, no, no, face the cabinet. Good.
我要你站在这里, 不, 不, 不, 面朝柜子。好了

92
00:06:48,534 --> 00:06:52,444
MAXTIBLE: Now, bend that.
现在, 掰弯那个

93
00:06:54,745 --> 00:07:00,222
<i>(Kemel strips off his waistcoat and shirt.)</i>
<i>(Kemel 脱下坎肩和衬衣)</i>

94
00:07:32,745 --> 00:07:36,222
<i>(Maxtible takes the bent bar and looks towards the cabinet.)</i>
<i>(Maxtible 拿过掰弯的铁棍, 往柜子方向望去)</i>

95
00:07:37,787 --> 00:07:45,267
MAXTIBLE: Excellent Kemel, excellent.
Now, you'll help me with these stools.
很好, Kemel, 很好。现在, 帮我弄一下这几个凳子

96
00:07:46,912 --> 00:07:53,111
<i>(Maxtible picks up a wooden plank and lays it across the stools.)</i>
<i>(Maxtible 拿过来一个厚木棍, 架在两个条凳之间)</i>

97
00:08:02,266 --> 00:08:07,020
MAXTIBLE: Now, Kemel. One blow. Break the plank!
现在, Kemel, 一次把这跟木头打断!

98
00:08:16,071 --> 00:08:25,186
MAXTIBLE: Very good Kemel. I'm very pleased with you. 
Now you can put on your jacket. Come over here.
很好, Kemel, 我对你很满意。现在你可以穿上你的夹克了。到这里来

99
00:08:25,235 --> 00:08:29,502
<i>(Maxtible puts the stools away.)</i>
<i>(Maxtible 把条凳挪开了)</i>

100
00:08:29,635 --> 00:08:34,502
MAXTIBLE: Now, I want you to listen carefully. See this man?
到这里来。现在, 我想要你听仔细了, 看到这个人了吗？

101
00:08:36,017 --> 00:08:39,292
MAXTIBLE: Now, I'm going to take you to a place that I want you to guard,
现在, 我要带你去一个地方, 期望你做好守卫工作

102
00:08:39,392 --> 00:08:43,892
MAXTIBLE: and this young man will try and get past you
and you are not to let him. Do you understand?
而这个年轻人会试图越过你, 你不能允许他这样做, 你明白吗？

103
00:08:44,317 --> 00:08:52,292
MAXTIBLE: Oh, he's an evil villain, Kemel, a cutthroat
who would gladly murder us all in our beds, if he could.
哦, 他是一个邪恶的恶棍, Kemel,
他会残忍地将我们所有人杀死在床上的, 如果他有机会的话

104
00:08:52,392 --> 00:08:55,892
MAXTIBLE: You will remember this man, hmm?
你要记住这个人, 嗯？

105
00:08:56,493 --> 00:08:59,496
MAXTIBLE: Right. Well, you come with me and I will direct you.
好了, 你跟我来, 我带你去

106
00:09:01,875 --> 00:09:05,415
<i>(They both leave.)</i>
<i>(他俩都离开了)</i>

107
00:09:06,375 --> 00:09:11,415
<i>(The Dalek comes out of the cabinet and looks at the bent iron bar.)</i>
<i>(Dalek 从柜子里面出来, 观察那根掰弯的铁棍)</i>

108
00:09:16,375 --> 00:09:20,415
<i>(Maxtible moves over to a candle and lights it.)</i>
<i>(Maxtible 走去拿了一根蜡烛, 把它点亮)</i>

109
00:09:29,875 --> 00:09:34,415
MAXTIBLE: You wait here. This is the entrance to the south wing of my house,
你在这里等着, 这里是我房子的南厢入口

110
00:09:34,875 --> 00:09:39,915
MAXTIBLE: and through here will pass the man I showed you in the picture.
图片里面那个人就会从这里过来,

111
00:09:40,075 --> 00:09:42,415
MAXTIBLE: The door itself is an obstacle.
这门就是一个屏障

112
00:09:41,875 --> 00:09:45,415
<i>(Maxtible presses the wall and it opens.)</i>
<i>(Maxtible 在墙上按了一下, 墙打开了)</i>

113
00:09:47,271 --> 00:09:48,365
MAXTIBLE: No, no, wait!
不, 不, 等等！

114
00:09:50,175 --> 00:09:56,415
<i>(Sharp metal spike lunge out across the entrance.)</i>
<i>(锋利的金属尖刺突然窜了出来, 封住了入口)</i>

115
00:10:01,175 --> 00:10:07,415
<i>(He presses a different part of the wall
and spikes slowly retract into the wall.)</i>
<i>(他在墙上另外一个位置按了一下, 尖刺慢慢缩了回去)</i>

116
00:10:08,712 --> 00:10:16,521
MAXTIBLE: Now, if he gets through here, you will deal with him. Go now.
现在, 如果他到这里来, 你要对付他。去吧

117
00:10:16,775 --> 00:10:20,415
<i>(Kemel goes through the alcove.)</i>
<i>(Kemel 穿过暗室)</i>

118
00:10:21,375 --> 00:10:26,815
<i>(Maxtible closes the alcove, blows out the candle and leaves.)</i>
<i>(Maxtible 关闭了暗室的门, 吹灭蜡烛, 离开了)</i>

119
00:10:27,457 --> 00:10:29,805
DALEK: We do not trust you.
我们不信任你

120
00:10:30,046 --> 00:10:31,110
DOCTOR: Then we're quits, aren't we?
那我们退出, 可以吗？

121
00:10:31,336 --> 00:10:33,554
DALEK: But we have your time machine.
但你的时间机器在我们手上

122
00:10:33,789 --> 00:10:34,519
DOCTOR: Yes.
是的

123
00:10:34,780 --> 00:10:36,273
DALEK: So, you will obey us.
所以, 你要服从我们

124
00:10:42,056 --> 00:10:44,916
DOCTOR: They want the "Human Factor", is that right?
他们想要“人类特质”, 对吗？

125
00:10:45,099 --> 00:10:46,607
Yes, that is what they want.
是的, 这就是他们想要的

126
00:10:46,760 --> 00:10:54,567
DOCTOR: Very complex. And you want to introduce
this "human factor" into the race of Daleks?
这很复杂。你们期望把“人类特质”加入到 Daleks 种族中去？

127
00:10:54,760 --> 00:11:02,591
DALEK: Yes, the conquest of humanity has eluded us.
The Daleks must know why.
是的, 人类的征服能力让我们很困惑。Daleks 必须明白为什么

128
00:11:02,806 --> 00:11:04,774
DOCTOR: But, why choose Jamie for this test?
但是, 为什么挑选 Jamie 做实验？

129
00:11:04,978 --> 00:11:08,076
DALEK: His travelling with you makes him unique.
他跟你一起旅行, 这让他变得独特

130
00:11:08,269 --> 00:11:09,434
DOCTOR: But why him? Why not me?
但为什么是他, 为什么不是我？

131
00:11:09,630 --> 00:11:10,518
DALEK: Request denied.
拒绝回答

132
00:11:10,700 --> 00:11:11,376
DOCTOR: Why?
为什么？

133
00:11:11,563 --> 00:11:16,551
DALEK: You have travelled too much through time.
You are more than human.
你在时间中旅行得太久了, 你不仅仅是个人类了

134
00:11:17,375 --> 00:11:18,488
DOCTOR: I see.
我明白了

135
00:11:20,520 --> 00:11:21,922
DOCTOR: What is this?
这是什么？

136
00:11:22,429 --> 00:11:25,832
MAXTIBLE: They have been brought from the Dalek planet.
他们是从 Dalek 星球带过来的

137
00:11:26,180 --> 00:11:27,067
DOCTOR: Skaro!
<i>(注: Daleks 的母星)</i>

138
00:11:27,575 --> 00:11:33,176
DALEK: Yes, their life force is dormant.
Before it is activated, we want...
是的。他们目前处于休眠状态, 激活之后, 我们想要。。。

139
00:11:34,031 --> 00:11:37,192
DOCTOR: You want the "human factor" introduced. I see.
你们想要引入“人类特质”, 我知道了

140
00:11:37,391 --> 00:11:38,667
DALEK: You will obey us!
你要服从我们！

141
00:11:38,866 --> 00:11:39,866
DOCTOR: I will make up my own mind!
我会自己拿主意！

142
00:11:40,004 --> 00:11:43,629
MAXTIBLE: Do not antagonize them, Doctor.
They will destroy your time machine!
不要激怒他们, 博士。他们会毁了你的时间机器的！

143
00:11:43,813 --> 00:11:50,054
MAXTIBLE: And if I agree, it means the creation of a race of super-Daleks!
但如果我同意, 那就意味着超级 Daleks 的诞生！

144
00:11:54,964 --> 00:12:00,875
DOCTOR: My TARDIS... I have no choice, do I?
Very well. I agree.
我的 TARDIS。。。我没有选择, 有吗？好吧, 我同意了

145
00:12:01,152 --> 00:12:06,312
DALEK: The human being with you must not be aware of the trial.
跟着你的那个人必须对这项实验不知情

146
00:12:06,672 --> 00:12:07,820
DOCTOR: I quite understand.
我很明白

147
00:12:08,011 --> 00:12:10,766
DALEK: Make him begin the test!
让他开始实验！

148
00:12:11,011 --> 00:12:16,766
<i>(The Dalek moves into the cabinet.)</i>
<i>(Dalek 回到了柜子里)</i>

149
00:12:20,890 --> 00:12:22,034
DOCTOR: What must Jamie do?
Jamie 必须干什么？

150
00:12:23,131 --> 00:12:27,445
DOCTOR: Attempt to rescue Waterfield's daughter.
尝试营救 Waterfield 的女儿

151
00:12:36,148 --> 00:12:36,806
MOLLIE: There we are, sir.

152
00:12:37,109 --> 00:12:37,976
TERRALL: Thank you, Mollie.
谢谢你, Mollie

153
00:12:38,695 --> 00:12:40,245
RUTH: Arthur, I'd like you to meet Mr. McCrimmon.
Arthur, 我引你见一下 McCrimmon 先生

154
00:12:41,039 --> 00:12:43,082
TERRALL: May I ask what you are doing in this house?
我能问问你在这个房子里面干什么吗？

155
00:12:43,410 --> 00:12:44,991
JAMIE: I was just about to ask you the same thing.
我也正要问你同一个问题

156
00:12:45,571 --> 00:12:47,546
RUTH: Oh, you gentlemen have been introduced?
哦, 有人已经介绍两位先生认识了？

157
00:12:47,726 --> 00:12:48,851
JAMIE: Aye, we've met.
是, 我们碰过面

158
00:12:49,558 --> 00:12:53,046
TERRALL: It seems, Ruth, your father has the oddest collection of house guests these days.
看起来, Ruth 小姐, 你父亲这几天招待了一大堆奇怪的客人啊

159
00:12:54,014 --> 00:12:55,718
RUTH: Now Arthur, please!
Arthur, 别这样

160
00:12:56,046 --> 00:12:58,069
RUTH: You must forgive him, Mr. McCrimmon.
你得原谅他, McCrimmon 先生

161
00:12:58,303 --> 00:12:59,519
JAMIE: Ah, it's becoming a habit.
啊, 都已经习惯了

162
00:12:59,767 --> 00:13:01,042
TERRALL: I don't care for insolence.
我并不太在意这些无礼的行为

163
00:13:01,249 --> 00:13:03,135
JAMIE: Well, I'm not keen on arrogance myself!
哈, 我也不太在乎那些自大的家伙

164
00:13:03,453 --> 00:13:06,112
RUTH: Why, you bite at each other as if you were old enemies!
为什么, 你们俩就好像宿敌一样要互相咬？

165
00:13:06,647 --> 00:13:08,214
JAMIE: I'm sorry if I seem rude.
如果我看起来比较粗鲁, 我很抱歉

166
00:13:08,471 --> 00:13:12,828
RUTH: Come, I want you to be friends.
Won't you be so, to please me?
好了, 我期望你们成为朋友。你们可以吗, 就给我点面子？

167
00:13:16,240 --> 00:13:23,189
RUTH: Arthur... Arthur, what is it?
Excuse me. Arthur! What's the matter?
Arthur... Arthur, 怎么了？ 对不起。Arthur！什么情况？

168
00:13:25,240 --> 00:13:29,189
<i>(Terrall and Ruth leave.)</i>
<i>(Terrall 和 Ruth 离开了)</i>

169
00:13:30,791 --> 00:13:31,798
MOLLIE: Sir?
先生？

170
00:13:32,060 --> 00:13:35,283
JAMIE: Yes?! Oh, I wish you'd call me Jamie.
什么事？ 哦, 我期望你叫我 Jamie

171
00:13:35,493 --> 00:13:37,849
MOLLIE: Oh, I couldn't do that sir. What would the master say?
噢, 我不能那样做, 先生。不知道主人会怎么说我呢

172
00:13:38,029 --> 00:13:41,010
JAMIE: Oh, who cares! Ah, What can I do for you?
哦, 谁在乎！啊, 有什么能帮到你的？

173
00:13:41,236 --> 00:13:45,756
MOLLIE: If you'd tell me where your bags are, sir -
yours and the Doctor's - I'll have them taken up to your room.
如果你能告诉我你的包裹在哪儿 —— 你和博士的 —— 我会让人把他们带到你的房间来的

174
00:13:45,994 --> 00:13:47,239
JAMIE: Aye. well, Mollie...
啊, 这个, Mollie...

175
00:13:47,408 --> 00:13:51,255
MOLLIE: Listen to me, "have them taken. "
I dare say I'll be doin' it meself!
听我说, 我说“让人带过来”, 其实我会亲自做的！

176
00:13:51,431 --> 00:13:54,077
JAMIE: You see, we didn't have time to pick up the luggage.
It'll be following.
你看, 我们并没有时间收拾行李, 过两天才会送来

177
00:13:54,315 --> 00:13:54,968
MOLLIE: Oh.
哦

178
00:13:55,310 --> 00:13:57,080
JAMIE: Why do you say that you'll be doing it yourself?
为什么你说你要自己做？

179
00:13:57,268 --> 00:14:00,397
MOLLIE: Well, they do say, sir, that the house is haunted.
哦, 他们说, 先生, 这房子闹鬼

180
00:14:00,568 --> 00:14:04,397
MOLLIE: Mr. Kitson, the butler, left.
And cook and the two footmen are complainin' again.
Kitson 先生, 我们的管家离开了。 厨师和两个杂役都在说这个

181
00:14:04,591 --> 00:14:05,261
JAMIE: Haunted?
闹鬼？

182
00:14:05,481 --> 00:14:09,767
MOLLIE: Mmm. But, I've never heard anything sir.
I sleep like a log and always have.
嗯。不过, 我从来没听到过什么, 先生。我睡觉跟一根木头似的, 总是这样

183
00:14:10,093 --> 00:14:12,138
JAMIE: Aye. well, I'm glad you've got over the fright you had.
啊, 这样。我很高兴你已经克服了恐惧

184
00:14:12,440 --> 00:14:17,873
JAMIE: Oh, yes, that horrible man.
Miss Ruth said it was all a game, but I dunno sir.
噢, 是的, 那个吓人的家伙。Ruth 小姐说只是个游戏, 不过我也搞不懂。

185
00:14:18,440 --> 00:14:22,873
MOLLIE: I've never fainted before, sir. Truly I haven't.
我以前从来没有晕倒过, 先生。真的没有

186
00:14:23,076 --> 00:14:25,135
JAMIE: Not "sir", "Jamie"!
不是“先生”, “Jamie”！

187
00:14:26,498 --> 00:14:28,029
JAMIE: Tell me about Arthur Terrall.
告诉我一些 Arthur Terrall 的情况

188
00:14:28,279 --> 00:14:29,674
MOLLIE: Miss Ruth's fiance, sir?
Ruth 小姐的未婚夫, 先生

189
00:14:29,908 --> 00:14:30,638
JAMIE: Aye.
啊

190
00:14:30,864 --> 00:14:34,318
MOLLIE: Oh, oh, he's a kind man, sir. Usually.
哦, 他是个好人, 先生。通常来说

191
00:14:34,555 --> 00:14:35,419
JAMIE: Usually?
通常来说？

192
00:14:35,618 --> 00:14:40,483
MOLLIE: Mmm. Well, when he's a bit odd or his temper's up,
as it has been lately,
嗯, 就是, 他有点怪, 或者脾气上来了, 就像最近那样

193
00:14:40,618 --> 00:14:43,083
MOLLIE: I says to meself "Inkerman" and then it's all right.
我跟自己说, 估计“英克曼人”就是那样

194
00:14:43,279 --> 00:14:44,001
JAMIE: "Inkerman"?
“英克曼人”？

195
00:14:44,200 --> 00:14:49,244
MOLLIE: Yes sir. 'e was out in the Crimea, 'e was.
They do say Mr. Terrall was wounded out there.
是的先生, 他是从克里米亚来的, 他是。他们的确说过 Terrall 在那里受了伤

196
00:14:49,400 --> 00:14:55,244
MOLLIE: Do you know, my uncle was killed at Inkerman, sir.
So, you see, I do know what it's like with soldiers.
你知道吗, 我叔叔就是在英克曼战死的, 先生。所以, 你看, 我还真知道士兵是怎样的
<i>(备注：1854-1856年, 俄国与英、法为争夺小亚细亚地区权利而爆发“克里米亚战争“)</i>

197
00:14:55,490 --> 00:14:59,278
MOLLIE: Oh... oh, I'm sorry sir. I didn't mean to...
哦。。。哦, 对不起先生。我不是有意的。。。

198
00:14:59,490 --> 00:15:02,778
MOLLIE: Well cook said to me that if I did some dusting it would be all right.
厨师跟我说, 我打扫打扫就可以了

199
00:15:02,990 --> 00:15:05,778
MOLLIE: Oh, you won't tell the master, will you?
That I... Ah, ah... Thank you. Sorry sir.
哦, 你不会告诉主人的, 是吗？那我。。。啊。。谢谢你, 对不起,先生

200
00:15:05,958 --> 00:15:07,977
DOCTOR: Sorry Mollie. Never mind, Mollie. That will do.
Yes, Mollie, thank you very much. It's all right, Mollie.
抱歉 Mollie, 不用在意, Moiilie, 这就行了, 好了, Mollie

201
00:15:08,258 --> 00:15:09,977
DOCTOR: I wouldn't dream of telling him. Thank you very much, Bye-bye.
我不会告诉他的, 很谢谢你, 拜拜

202
00:15:14,176 --> 00:15:18,833
DOCTOR: Hmm, you'll have to brush up on your history.
I can't be around to cover up for you all the time.
呜, 你得刷新一下你的历史知识了。我不可能总在你身边替你补课
<i>(备注: Jamie 是172x年诞生的, 174x年开始跟随博士旅行, 所以他对后面的历史知道得不多)</i>

203
00:15:19,203 --> 00:15:24,413
DOCTOR: Now then, in the Crimean War, the English, the French
and the Turks fought the Russians...
这一次, 克里米亚战争, 英国人、法国人和土耳其人一起跟俄国人打

204
00:15:24,589 --> 00:15:25,812
JAMIE: Oh, forget about all that!
哦, 忘了那些吧

205
00:15:25,957 --> 00:15:31,590
DOCTOR: Oh, I thought you'd be interested. I watched
the Charge of the Light Brigade. Magnificent folly...
哦, 我以为你会感兴趣。我可见过轻骑兵发起的冲锋, 那可真是愚蠢。。。
<i>(备注: 此处特指1854年10月克里米亚战争巴拉克拉瓦战役中,
英国轻骑兵向俄军发起的冲锋, 因命令传达错误而伤亡惨重。
因诗歌 The Charge of the Light Brigade 而受后人铭记)</i>

206
00:15:31,757 --> 00:15:33,043
DOCTOR: Look, where've you been?
我说, 你都去哪儿了？

207
00:15:33,196 --> 00:15:34,129
DOCTOR: Oh, just looking around.
哦, 只是四处看看

208
00:15:34,281 --> 00:15:35,285
JAMIE: Aye. What for? The TARDIS?!
啊, 看什么？TARDIS 吗？

209
00:15:36,543 --> 00:15:38,570
DOCTOR: Jamie, you're in a temper!
Jamie, 你在闹脾气啊

210
00:15:38,750 --> 00:15:43,691
JAMIE: Oh, am I? Is that bad then? Does that mean I won't
be co-operative - I won't do everything I'm told?
哦, 是吗？这很糟糕吧？是不是意味着我不会乖乖听话了？不会说什么我就做什么了？

211
00:15:44,030 --> 00:15:44,823
DOCTOR: What was that?
这是什么话？

212
00:15:44,991 --> 00:15:46,210
JAMIE: I overheard you and Waterfield!
我听到了你和 Waterfield 的对话！

213
00:15:46,354 --> 00:15:47,358
DOCTOR: You were eavesdropping!
你居然在偷听！

214
00:15:47,492 --> 00:15:48,676
JAMIE: Well, whatever it is, I don't like what you're doing.
不管怎样, 我不喜欢你现在做的事

215
00:15:48,808 --> 00:15:49,574
DOCTOR: Now you listen to me...!
你听我说。。。！

216
00:15:49,737 --> 00:15:52,394
JAMIE: No, Doctor, you're forgetting the TARDIS was stolen
and a man was murdered!
不, 博士, 你已经忘记 TARDIS 被偷了, 还有人被杀了

217
00:15:52,737 --> 00:15:55,394
JAMIE:  Now, how am I supposed to tell when I see
you as friendly as you like with the murderer!
现在, 我看见你跟杀人凶手在一起跟朋友似的, 你让我怎么想呢？

218
00:15:55,616 --> 00:15:57,672
DOCTOR: Waterfield did not murder that man!
Waterfield 没有杀那个人！

219
00:15:57,828 --> 00:16:00,492
JAMIE: All right then, but he stole the TARDIS
and that still makes him a thief!
那好, 但他偷了 TARDIS, 他仍然还是一个小偷！

220
00:16:00,655 --> 00:16:01,727
DOCTOR: The Daleks forced him to!
Daleks 强迫他干的

221
00:16:01,862 --> 00:16:04,522
JAMIE: The Daleks! You keep telling me about the Daleks,
and I haven't even seen one!
Daleks！ 你一直跟我说 Daleks, 但我一个没见着。

222
00:16:04,662 --> 00:16:05,922
JAMIE: You're always on about them, but where are they?!
你不停地说, 但他们在哪儿呢？

223
00:16:06,084 --> 00:16:06,702
DOCTOR: Now you listen to me...!
你得听我说啊。。。！

224
00:16:06,867 --> 00:16:09,071
JAMIE: No, you'll not get round me this time, Doctor.
不, 这次你别想忽悠我了, 博士

225
00:16:09,267 --> 00:16:10,671
DOCTOR: You're up to something with Waterfield and Maxtible.
你跟 Waterfield 还有 Maxtible 在搞些什么

226
00:16:10,867 --> 00:16:13,671
JAMIE: Now what is it? Some scientific invention?!
到底是什么呢? 某种科学发明吗？！

227
00:16:14,215 --> 00:16:15,510
JAMIE: Ah, here's your friend.
啊, 你的朋友来了

228
00:16:15,682 --> 00:16:16,654
DOCTOR: Just a little argument.
只是一点小争论

229
00:16:16,959 --> 00:16:18,404
WATERFIELD: I heard voices raised.
我听着声音有点大了

230
00:16:18,579 --> 00:16:19,791
JAMIE: That's not all you'll hear!
你听见的才不止这点呢

231
00:16:19,959 --> 00:16:22,291
DOCTOR: Jamie seems to think that I'm lying to him.
Jamie 似乎认为我在欺骗他

232
00:16:22,489 --> 00:16:23,268
JAMIE: Well, aren't you?!
怎么, 没有吗？

233
00:16:23,405 --> 00:16:24,771
DOCTOR: He doesn't believe the Daleks are here.
他并不相信 Daleks 就在这里

234
00:16:24,955 --> 00:16:25,771
WATERFIELD: It's the truth.
这是事实

235
00:16:25,970 --> 00:16:29,244
JAMIE: Aye, the truth you told Arthur Terrall, maybe
- that your daughter was in Paris!
啊, 你还把事实告诉了 Arthur Terrall —— 你的女儿在巴黎！

236
00:16:29,442 --> 00:16:30,595
WATERFIELD: I had to tell him that.
我只能那样跟他说

237
00:16:30,775 --> 00:16:32,275
JAMIE: So, you've got another story to tell me?
所以, 你还有另外一个故事是给我的罗？

238
00:16:32,511 --> 00:16:37,352
WATERFIELD: I tell you that the Daleks are holding my daughter
prisoner in the south wing of this house, Mr. McCrimmon.
我跟你说, Daleks 现在把我的女儿关押在了这栋房子的南面, McCrimmon 先生

239
00:16:37,509 --> 00:16:40,251
JAMIE: Then why don't you try and get her back, eh?!
What are you doing?!
那你怎么不试着把她救回来, 嗯？你在忙些什么？

240
00:16:40,412 --> 00:16:42,654
DOCTOR: : Well, what can I do? Now, be... be fair Jamie.
我能怎么做？现在。。。理智点 Jamie

241
00:16:42,912 --> 00:16:47,254
DOCTOR: Waterfield's tied hand and foot because of his daughter
and we're tied hand and foot because of the TARDIS!
Waterfield 因为他女儿而投鼠忌器, 我们因为 TARDIS 而束手束脚

242
00:16:47,447 --> 00:16:49,951
JAMIE: Aye, and that's all you can think about, isn't it?
The TARDIS?
啊, 你能想到的就只有这个, TARDIS, 是吗?

243
00:16:50,047 --> 00:16:52,951
JAMIE: Well, you can all stand around doing nothing.
I'm sick to death of it!
你就站在那里什么也不做？我恶心死了！

244
00:16:53,075 --> 00:16:54,098
DOCTOR: Now just where are you going?
你现在要去哪儿？

245
00:16:54,244 --> 00:16:56,599
JAMIE: To be by myself for a bit. Do you mind?
一个人呆一会儿, 你管得着吗？

246
00:16:56,744 --> 00:17:01,978
DOCTOR: No, not a bit. But, one word of warning.
Don't you try to be a one-man army. You leave well alone.
不, 管不着。但警告你一句话, 别想一个人逞英雄。你别管这事

247
00:17:02,244 --> 00:17:06,978
DOCTOR: I won't have you ruining everything trying to rescue
Victoria Waterfield. Now, you understand?!
我不能允许你为了救 Victoria Waterfield 而毁了一切, 你听明白了没有？！

248
00:17:10,965 --> 00:17:14,371
WATERFIELD: Well, are you sure you didn't go a little too far, Doctor?
唉, 你确定这样是不是有点过火了, 博士？

249
00:17:14,778 --> 00:17:21,320
DOCTOR: Adding a little fuel to the fire.
Tell Maxtible that I'll be along to his laboratory shortly.
要火上浇点油。告诉 Maxtible 我很快就到他的实验室去

250
00:17:21,465 --> 00:17:22,645
WATERFIELD: Oh, very well, Doctor. If you're sure.
哦, 好吧, 博士。如果你确定的话

251
00:17:22,790 --> 00:17:27,311
DOCTOR: Oh yes, quite sure. Once our young friend has cooled
his heels a bit, he'll launch off on his own.
是的, 很确定。一旦我们的小朋友冷静一点, 他就会自己开始行动了

252
00:17:27,790 --> 00:17:31,311
DOCTOR: And you dropped the hint about the south wing beautifully.
而且你也很漂亮地把南厢房的线索传递给他了

253
00:17:38,246 --> 00:17:44,456
TERRALL: Well, what is it? You wanted to see me?
怎么, 什么事？你想要见我？

254
00:17:46,156 --> 00:17:47,632
TOBY: Very good of you to talk to me, gov'nor.
你愿意跟我谈谈太好了, 先生

255
00:17:47,800 --> 00:17:50,398
TERRALL: Well, never mind all that.
I'll give you two minutes, no more.
好了, 别提这个了。我之给你两分钟, 多了没有

256
00:17:50,668 --> 00:17:52,324
TOBY: I want me rights. No more, no less.
我想要我的权利, 不多要, 也不能少给

257
00:17:52,656 --> 00:17:54,096
TERRALL: What do you mean, "rights"?
你什么意思, “权利”？

258
00:17:54,409 --> 00:17:56,475
TOBY: 'alf a guinea, you gave me, and it ain't what we said.
你刚才就给了半个基尼, 这不是我们之前说好的

259
00:17:56,929 --> 00:17:58,687
TERRALL: You were lucky to get anything.
你还能拿到一点就不错了

260
00:17:59,194 --> 00:18:00,159
TOBY: That ain't fair!
这不公平

261
00:18:00,367 --> 00:18:04,373
TERRALL: You'll get no more from me. I warn you!
Keep away from this house, and this property. 
你别想从我这里得到更多钱。我警告你, 离这个房子远点儿

262
00:18:03,567 --> 00:18:06,773
TERRALL: Find the nearest road to London and take it!
找到去伦敦的路, 走吧

263
00:18:08,124 --> 00:18:12,928
TOBY: Oh, yeah, London, sir. Yeah, I daresay
I could earn something for me stories there.
哦, 是啊, 伦敦, 先生。好啊, 我敢说, 到了那里我只凭讲故事就可以挣到钱啦

264
00:18:13,300 --> 00:18:13,924
TERRALL: Stories?
故事？

265
00:18:14,108 --> 00:18:18,878
TOBY: Oh, I won't detain an important gentleman like yourself.
Like as not me two minutes is up anyway.
哦, 我可不敢再耽误您这样的绅士了。不管喜欢不喜欢, 我的两分钟已经到了

266
00:18:19,038 --> 00:18:20,144
TERRALL: What do you mean, "stories"?
你什么意思, “讲故事”？

267
00:18:20,266 --> 00:18:21,999
TOBY: Ah, it's all right, sir. I'll take a stroll to London...
啊, 没事, 先生。我得上路去伦敦了。。。

268
00:18:22,139 --> 00:18:23,674
TERRALL: Don't play with me!
别跟我玩花样！

269
00:18:23,913 --> 00:18:29,584
TOBY: Get off me! If you must know, there's plenty
who'd pay to hear what I've got to tell 'em.
把手拿开！如果你非得知道, 有好多人愿意付钱听我给他们讲呢

270
00:18:29,790 --> 00:18:30,610
TERRALL: Indeed?
真的？

271
00:18:30,817 --> 00:18:35,881
TOBY: Yeah. You blows too hot and cold for me
- tellin' me this one minute and that the next, and not payin' up.
是啊, 你这一会儿阴一会儿晴, 一会儿这么说, 一会儿又那么说, 还不付钱

272
00:18:36,048 --> 00:18:36,993
TERRALL: You know nothing.
你什么也不知道

273
00:18:37,146 --> 00:18:38,966
TOBY: Don't I though?
我不知道吗, 哈？

274
00:18:39,477 --> 00:18:40,946
TERRALL: Hmm. Who'd believe you anyway?
唔, 谁会信你呢？

275
00:18:41,103 --> 00:18:42,372
TOBY: Pay me off, and there's the end of it!
把钱付了, 这事儿就算完了

276
00:18:42,528 --> 00:18:45,485
TERRALL: Oh, blackmail is it?! Get out!
噢, 勒索是吗？ 滚出去！

277
00:18:54,128 --> 00:18:59,485
<i>(As Terrall lies unconscious, Toby goes through his pockets.)</i>
<i>(Terrall 躺在地上不省人事, Toby 趁机翻他的口袋)</i>

278
00:19:00,128 --> 00:19:05,485
<i>(Toby finds some coins and a bunch of keys.)</i>
<i>(Toby 找了几个硬币和一串钥匙)</i>

279
00:19:10,136 --> 00:19:16,335
TOBY: Maybe I don't know much to tell, but I'll wager
I'll find something in the house that's worth me trouble.
也许我知道得不多, 但我打赌我能在这房子里找到点什么, 肯定有料

280
00:19:16,536 --> 00:19:18,335
TOBY: So, I'll say thank ya, Mr. Terrall, sir!
那, 我就说声谢谢你了, Terrall 先生

281
00:19:45,811 --> 00:19:49,654
<i>(Mollie enters the sitting room carrying an old map.</i>
<i>(Mollie 进了客厅, 带着一份旧地图)</i>

282
00:19:50,526 --> 00:19:52,108
JAMIE: It's only me, Mollie!
是我, Mollie!

283
00:19:53,165 --> 00:19:56,707
MOLLIE: It's over here, sir. I took it from the master's study.
就在这里, 先生。我从主人的书房里面拿出来的

284
00:19:56,898 --> 00:19:58,559
JAMIE: It's marvellous. Thank you!
这太棒了, 谢谢你！

285
00:19:58,877 --> 00:20:01,590
MOLLIE: 'ere, is this what you wanted?
这里, 这是你想要的吗？

286
00:20:00,877 --> 00:20:05,590
<i>(She hands Jamie a plan of the house.)</i>
<i>(她递给 Jamie 一份这栋房子的平面图)</i>

287
00:20:03,437 --> 00:20:09,063
JAMIE: Perfect, yes. Let's see, umm...
this is the south wing here?
非常好, 是的, 让我看一下, 嗯。。。这里是南厢房吗？

288
00:20:09,434 --> 00:20:10,994
MOLLIE: Yes sir, but it's been closed off.
是的先生, 但这里被封了

289
00:20:11,181 --> 00:20:11,954
JAMIE: Completely?
完全封了？

290
00:20:12,115 --> 00:20:17,044
MOLLIE: Oh, no sir. Only 'cause of some repairs
about a twelve-month back. But the door may be locked.
哦, 不是, 先生。只是一些修缮工作, 都快一年了。不过门可能被锁住了

291
00:20:17,243 --> 00:20:18,130
JAMIE: Can you show me?
你能指给我看一下吗？

292
00:20:18,392 --> 00:20:25,150
MOLLIE: All right. What're you gonna do, sir?
行。你打算做什么, 先生？

293
00:20:20,392 --> 00:20:25,650
<i>(Jamie folds up the plan to take with him.)</i>
<i>(Jamie 折叠起地图, 带到身上)</i>

294
00:20:25,818 --> 00:20:27,545
JAMIE: Off to hunt a few wee ghosties, Mollie.
去抓几个小鬼, Mollie

295
00:20:30,186 --> 00:20:36,787
DOCTOR: Every single one of Jamie's reactions
will be recorded on these Dalek machines?
Jamie 的每个动作都会在 Dalek 的这些机器上记录下来？

296
00:20:37,165 --> 00:20:42,585
MAXTIBLE: And then transformed into thought patterns
on silver wire. A wonderful creation!
然后再转化成思维模型, 存储到银线。多么漂亮的发明！

297
00:20:42,858 --> 00:20:49,689
DALEK: It is for you, Doctor, to select the major feelings
to make up this "human factor".
这是为你准备的, 博士, 你可以用它来挑选出那些组成“人类特质”的主要情感

298
00:20:49,950 --> 00:20:51,074
DOCTOR: Oh, yes. I quite understand.
哦, 是的, 我完全明白

299
00:20:51,310 --> 00:20:54,540
MAXTIBLE: We can rely on the Doctor to give us all cooperation.
我们可以信赖博士给予我们全面的合作

300
00:20:54,708 --> 00:20:57,377
DALEK: We shall watch your every move.
我们会盯着你的一举一动

301
00:20:57,704 --> 00:21:02,974
DOCTOR: I'm sure you will.
And every step of Jamie's progress will be covered?
我确信你们会这样的。Jamie 的每一步也会包含在内吧？

302
00:21:03,401 --> 00:21:06,900
<i>(Another Dalek enters.)</i>
<i>(又一个 Dalek 进来了)</i>

303
00:21:03,404 --> 00:21:04,353
DALEK: Yes.
是的

304
00:21:06,396 --> 00:21:09,681
DALEK: The young human being is on his way.
这位年轻人已经在路上了

305
00:21:10,410 --> 00:21:12,921
DOCTOR: Then the recording machines can be set in action.
那么录制设备就可以开启了

306
00:21:21,829 --> 00:21:22,552
JAMIE: Here!
这里

307
00:21:22,743 --> 00:21:25,013
MOLLIE: Yes, sir. I once remember the master stepping away from here.
是的, 先生。我记得有一次主人就从这里走过去的

308
00:21:25,243 --> 00:21:29,013
MOLLIE: When he saw me, he was very cross and told me to keep away.
他看见我的时候非常生气, 让我离开

309
00:21:29,192 --> 00:21:30,028
JAMIE: I see.
我明白了

310
00:21:31,192 --> 00:21:35,028
<i>(Jamie examines the back of the alcove.)</i>
<i>(Jamie 检查壁橱的后面)</i>

311
00:21:42,192 --> 00:21:47,528
<i>(Toby has entered Maxtible's workroom, and is looking around.)</i>
<i>(Toby 已经进入了 Maxtible 的工作室, 正在四处摸索)</i>

312
00:21:58,192 --> 00:22:02,528
<i>(A Daleks is watching him.)</i>
<i>(一个 Dalek 注视着他)</i>

313
00:22:14,117 --> 00:22:16,089
MOLLIE: What was that? What was that?!
那是什么？那是什么？

314
00:22:16,338 --> 00:22:19,366
JAMIE: That was no ghost, Mollie, that's for sure.
That was a human voice!
那不是鬼, Mollie, 这是肯定的。那是一个人的声音！

315
00:22:19,700 --> 00:22:20,627
MOLLIE: Oh, sir!
哦, 先生！

316
00:22:20,878 --> 00:22:23,897
JAMIE: Look Mollie, take the candle and go back to your room.
Will you do that?
你看, Mollie, 拿着蜡烛, 回到你的房间去。你可以吗？

317
00:22:24,085 --> 00:22:24,624
MOLLIE: Yes sir.
是的先生

318
00:22:24,843 --> 00:22:25,811
JAMIE: Now, do you want me to see you safely there?
那, 你期望我陪你过去, 以确保你安全到达吗？

319
00:22:25,976 --> 00:22:27,718
MOLLIE: No, no. I'll be all right.
不, 不用, 我没事的

320
00:22:36,176 --> 00:22:41,718
<i>(Jamie begins to examine the alcove area.)</i>
<i>(杰米开始检查壁橱区)</i>

321
00:22:54,176 --> 00:23:01,118
<i>(He spots grease marks on the wall.)</i>
<i>(他发现墙上有油脂痕迹)</i>

322
00:23:02,176 --> 00:23:06,818
<i>(Jamie presses the wall and the alove door opens.)</i>
<i>(杰米按了下墙壁, 壁橱门打开了)</i>

323
00:23:11,176 --> 00:23:17,818
<i>(The metal spikes swing down across the entrance.)</i>
<i>(金属尖刺戳了下来, 挡住了入口)</i>

324
00:23:23,176 --> 00:23:29,818
<i>(Jamie ducks underneath the spikes and through the alcove door.)</i>
<i>(杰米冒着腰, 躲着尖刺, 进了暗室的门)</i>

325
00:23:36,176 --> 00:23:42,818
<i>(Jamie is walking slowly along a corridor.)</i>
<i>(Jamie 沿着走廊慢慢地走着)</i>

326
00:23:59,853 --> 00:24:02,589
Hello. Who are you?
JAMIE: 你好, 你是谁？

